    "summary": "Who am I: passionate about research, interested in people, and moved by injustice. I am a problem solver, good at analyzing situations, and able to identify where problems lie and opportunities are. I am a social person, which, together with my sense of humour, enables me to work and communicate easily with a variety of people. I have a hands-on mentality and will make sure to finish projects well. \n\nResearch interests: food security and food system transformations. Understanding how food gets from farmers to consumers - the organization, transformation and sustainability of market channels such as informal traders, contract farming with processors, and cooperatives. As well as evaluating interventions and project governance for food system transformation, using impact evaluation and realist evaluation.\n\nExperience: both qualitative and quantitative research methods, research project management, extensive field experience in Africa (Uganda, Kenya, Ghana, South Africa) and South America (Ecuador)",
